telligent machines. Morally justified hierarchies can and should govern different spheres of our social lives, though these will be very different from the unjust hierarchies that have governed us in the past.A vigorous, systematic defense of hierarchy in the modern world, Just Hierarchy examines how hierarchical social relations can have a useful purpose, not only in personal domains but also in larger political realms.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aHierarchieszChina. 0aSocial groupszChina. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Political.2bisacsh  aAgainst Political Equality: The Confucian Case.  aAncient Chinese Thought, Modern Chinese Power.  aCommunist.  aConfucian Perfectionism: A Political Philosophy for Modern Times.  aJoseph Chan.  aMarx.  aPolitical thought.  aPrinceton-China Series.  aSilicon Valley.  aTongdong Bai.  aYan Xuetong.  aancient China.  aancient India.  aartificial intelligence.  acommunism.  acompetitive elections.  acontext.  ademocracy.  adomesticated.  aeating animals.  aegalitarianism.  aequal.  aequality.  aethics.  aexploit.  aexploitation.  afamily members.  afriends.  aglobal order.  ahousekeepers.  ahumane.  aliberal.  alovers.  ameritocracy.  apower.  arelationships.  asubordinate.  asubordination.  asystem.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPrinceton University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311074973140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780691239545?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780691239545423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780691239545/original  a978-3-11-074973-1  Princeton University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyte